description.narrative: UNICEF staff and partners are provided guidance, tools and resources to effectively design/plan, manage, monitor and evaluate the programme, including in the humanitarian situation., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Cross-Sectoral - Planning And Programme Reviews. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The country programme is effectively coordinated, managed and supported to achieve results for children

description.narrative: In 2021 UNICEF Ukraine country office prioritize its work for the preparation of the new Country Programme Document ;(CPD) 2023-2027. Comprehensive Situation Analysis of Children and Adolescent in Ukraine was elaborated. Draft Programme Rational for the CPD was developed and submitted to civil society organizations, Government partners as well as Regional Office for review. HACT assurance activities 100% achieved and proceed in e-tools. New Protection from Sexual Exploitation and Abuse (PSEA) module in e-Tools was introduced and all active implemented partners were assessd ;and got risk rating in e-tools with action plan. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
